The paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it proposes a method for encoding local features into a discriminative global descriptor, which is a common problem in AI. 

The paper may belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as place recognition is an important problem in robotics, especially for autonomous navigation. 

Finally, the paper may belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category as it uses the term "contextual attention" in the title, which is a common term in NLP. However, this is less likely as the paper does not deal with natural language processing.
